Drain pineapple well; reserve 1/2 cup juice. Beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy in large bowl. Beat in egg, crushed pineapple and reserved juice. Combine oats, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt; raisins and almonds in medium bowl. Stir into pineapple mixture. Drop by heaping tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheets. Shape with back of spoon. Bake at 350 degrees F., 20 to 25 minutes or until golden. Cool on wire racks.